\begin_layout Subsection
Usage
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
eLyXer can be invoked from the command line as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quotation

\family typewriter
$ elyxer.py [source file] [destination file]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the source file is omitted then 
\family typewriter
STDIN
\family default
 is used; likewise, if no destination file is specified eLyXer will output
 to 
\family typewriter
STDOUT
\family default
.
 This allows its use in pipes and other flexible configurations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Examples:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quotation

\family typewriter
$ elyxer.py file.lyx file.html
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
converts 
\family typewriter
file.lyx
\family default
 to 
\family typewriter
file.html
\family default
.
 Debug messages are shown.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quotation

\family typewriter
$ cat file.lyx | elyxer.py > file.html
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
converts 
\family typewriter
file.lyx
\family default
 to 
\family typewriter
file.html
\family default
, as before.
 This time debug messages are not shown.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quotation

\family typewriter
$ elyxer.py file.lyx | grep "<blockquote>" | wc
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
counts all blockquote paragraphs.
