\begin_layout Subsection
Resources
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
eLyXer should be quite fast on contemporary hardware.
 On my 1st-gen Asus Eee (with its underpowered 800MHz Celeron processor
 -- underclocked to 570MHz), eLyXer can convert ~200 pages of LyX text in
 just over 6 seconds.
 Performance is fairly lineal: 200 pages take 
\begin_inset Formula $10\times$
\end_inset

 as long as 20, so there are no artificial bottlenecks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Memory usage stays low even when processing large documents, since conversion
 is done on the fly.
\end_layout

