\begin_layout Section
Extending eLyXer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
eLyXer does not at the moment support all LyX features; it will happily
 stop processing whenever it finds an unknown command.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What can I do if eLyXer refuses to work with my LyX file? Worry not! Its
 flexible approach via containers, parsers and outputs allows anyone to
 write support for the missing command.
 eLyXer is written in Python so that it does not need to be compiled; its
 code is interpreted on the fly.
 It requires Python 2.5.x; at the moment there are no plans to migrate to
 Python 2.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See the accompanying developer guide to learn how to extend eLyXer for your
 own purposes.
\end_layout

